[[typeAnnotation]]\
An <<Annotation>> is a statement that declares a variable to have a certain <<Type>> or a <<Type>> to have a certain <<Kind>>.\
\
For example,\
[listing]\
alpha:all t ~~~ (t)=>string\
\
is a <<TypeAnnotation>>, whereas\
[listing]\
el :: type\
\
is a <<KindAnnotation>>.\
\
[[typeAnnotationFig]]\
